      <item>
        <title>Deployment issue with Vercel</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[juanma]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/mh123">@mh123</a></p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="mh123" data-post="6" data-topic="4237">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://community.frontity.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/a88e57/40.png" class="avatar"> mh123:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Does this makes sense? I lost several hours on this today, debugging.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Yes, it makes totally sense. The <code>package-lock.json</code> keep the dependencies locations so it also need to be removed for a complete re-install.</p>
<p>We’ve detected this is not very clear for the final users and we’re working on this (both the documentation and the framework) so the final users don’t have to worry about this.</p>
<p>Here you have some related threads:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/cant-run-site-on-localhost-invalid-hook-call/4185/17" class="inline-onebox">Can't run site on localhost - Invalid hook call - #17 by juanma</a></li>
<li><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/i-am-started-getting-error-typeerror-cannot-read-property-add-of-undefined/1975/18" class="inline-onebox">I am started getting error "TypeError: Cannot read property 'add' of undefined" - #18 by David</a></li>
</ul>
<p>And here’s the FD created to try to fix this:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/detect-node-modules-under-packages-folder-remove-them-and-launch-reinstall-from-root/4238" class="inline-onebox">Detect "node-modules" under "packages" folder, remove them and launch reinstall from root</a></li>
</ul>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/deployment-issue-with-vercel/4237/7">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
